hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: Sample Name
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: The name of this profile (used in the Indicators of Compromise report)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: Sleep Time
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Default sleep time (in milliseconds)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: Jitter
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Default jitter factor (0-99)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: Data Jitter
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Append random-length string (up to data_jitter value) to http-get and http-post server output.

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: Beacon User Agent
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Default User-Agent for HTTP comms.
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.defaultValue: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/42.0.2311.135 Safari/537.36 Edge/12.246

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: HTTPS Certificate Type
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Sets https-certificate values to be modified (Default: Self Signed) vs keystore and password (Disable for keystore and password)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: TCP Port
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Default TCP Beacon listen port

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Random TCP Frame Header
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Prepend random header to TCP Beacon messages

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: SMB Beacon Pipe Name
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Name of pipe for SMB sessions. Each # is replaced with a random hex value.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: SMB Beacon Pipe Name Stager
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Name of pipe for SMB stagr. Each # is replaced with a random hex value.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Random SMB Frame Header
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Prepend random header to SMB Beacon messages

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon DNS Idle
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: IP address used to indicate no tasks are available to DNS Beacon; Mask for other DNS C2 values

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon DNS Max TXT
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Maximum length of DNS TXT responses for tasks (0-255)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon DNS Sleep
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Force a sleep prior to each individual DNS request. (In milliseconds)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon DNS TTL
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: TTL for DNS replies

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon Max DNS
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Maximum length of hostname when uploading data over DNS (0-255)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon DNS Stager Prepend
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Prepend text to payload stage delivered to DNS TXT record stager

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon DNS Stager Subhost
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Subdomain used by DNS TXT record stager.

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon Beacon
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: DNS subhost prefix used for beaconing requests. (lowercase text)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon GETA
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: DNS subhost prefix used for A record requests (lowercase text)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon GET AAAA
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: DNS subhost prefix used for AAAA record requests (lowercase text)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon GET TXT
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: DNS subhost prefix used for TXT record requests (lowercase text)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon PUT Meta Data
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: DNS subhost prefix used for metadata requests (lowercase text)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon PUT Output
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: DNS subhost prefix used for output requests (lowercase text)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: DNS Beacon NS Response
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: How to process NS Record requests. "drop" does not respond to the request (default), "idle" responds with A record for IP address from "dns_idle", "zero" responds with A record for 0.0.0.0

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: SSH Banner
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: SSH client banner

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: SSH Pipename
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Name of pipe for SSH sessions. Each # is replaced with a random hex value. A's will be replaced with random chars

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: HTTP Stager URI x86
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: x86 payload stage URI

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: HTTP Stager URI x64
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: x64 payload stage URI

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex Spawn To x86
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Control the default temporary process Beacon will spawn for its post-exploitation features. (x86)

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex Spawn To x64
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Control the default temporary process Beacon will spawn for its post-exploitation features. (x64)

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex Obfuscate
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Scrambles the content of the post-ex DLLs and settles the post-ex capability into memory in a more OPSEC-safe way.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex Smartinject
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Directs Beacon to embed key function pointers, like GetProcAddress and LoadLibrary, into its same-architecture post-ex DLLs. This allows post-ex DLLs to bootstrap themselves in a new process without shellcode-like behavior that is detected and mitigated by watching memory accesses to the PEB and kernel32.dll.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex AMSI Disable
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Directs powerpick, execute-assembly, and psinject to patch the AmsiScanBuffer function before loading .NET or PowerShell code.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex Pipename
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Default name of pipe to use for SMB Beacon’s post exploitation activities. Each # is replaced with a random hex value.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Post Ex Keylogger
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: The GetAsyncKeyState option (default) uses the GetAsyncKeyState API to observe keystrokes. The SetWindowsHookEx option uses SetWindowsHookEx to observe keystrokes.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Allocator Settings
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: The preferred method to allocate memory in the current process to execute a BOF. Specify VirtualAlloc, MapViewOfFile, or HeapAlloc.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Memory Indicator Stomp PE
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Ask ReflectiveLoader to stomp MZ, PE, and e_lfanew values after it loads Beacon payload

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Memory Indicator Obfuscate
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Obfuscate the Reflective DLL’s import table, overwrite unused header content, and ask ReflectiveLoader to copy Beacon to new memory without its DLL headers. Review sleepmask and UDRL considerations for obfuscate

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Memory Indicator Stage Cleanup
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Ask Beacon to attempt to free memory associated with the Reflective DLL package that initialized it.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Memory Indicator Sleep Mask
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Obfuscate Beacon and it's heap, in-memory, prior to sleeping.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Memory Indicator Smart Inject
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Use embedded function pointer hints to bootstrap Beacon agent without walking kernel32 EAT

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: Memory Indicator Name
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: The Exported name of the Beacon DLL

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Proc Injection BOF Allocator
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: The preferred method to allocate memory in the current process to execute a BOF. Specify VirtualAlloc, MapViewOfFile, or HeapAlloc.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: Proc Injection Reuse Mem
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: Reuse the allocated memory for subsequent BOF executions otherwise release the memory. Memory will be cleared when not in use. If the available amount of memory is not large enough it will be released and allocated with the larger size.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Proc Injection Allocator
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: The preferred method to allocate memory in the remote process. Specify VirtualAllocEx or NtMapViewOfSection. The NtMapViewOfSection option is for same-architecture injection only. VirtualAllocEx is always used for cross-arch memory allocations.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: Proc Injection Min Alloc
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Minimum amount of memory to request for injected or BOF content.

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: HTTP Config Trust XForward
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: This option decides if Cobalt Strike uses the X-Forwarded-For HTTP header to determine the remote address of a request. Use this option if your Cobalt Strike server is behind an HTTP redirector.

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: HTTP GET URI
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Transaction URI

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: HTTP POST URI
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Transaction URI
